datetime-display
================

Scope
-----
Rules for displaying timestamps in the SPA (tables, charts, tooltips) so the UI uses a consistent, local-time format.

Rule
----
- Use `formatLocalDateTime` in `frontend/src/utils/formatLocalDateTime.ts` for all displayed instants.
- Formatting must be: DD/MM/YY HH.mm.ss.fff (24-hour clock, millisecond precision) using the browser local timezone.

Examples & guidance
-------------------
- Table columns, chart tooltips, and any user-facing logs in the SPA must call `formatLocalDateTime(date)` rather than rolling a custom formatter.
- `datetime-local` form inputs remain `yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm` as required by HTML; use `formatLocalDateTime` only for display/UI labels.

Why
---
Consistent format across the app improves readability for users in the target regions and avoids mixing server UTC formatting into the UI.

Note
----
If you need a different presentation for a specific component (relative time, short date only), create a new helper in `frontend/src/utils/` and explain the reason in a short code comment pointing to this rule.

